					<head>Commentary</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85013597" rend="visible">
						<summary>The commentary of Gersonides (Leṿi ben Gershom aka Ralbag) on the book of Proverbs, with the punctuated and accentuated biblical text.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he">Hebrew</textLang>
						<msItem n="0" rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85013597">
							<locus from="1r" to="109v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Perush Mishle</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">פרוש משלי</title>
							<author key="http://viaf.org/viaf/59118174">
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/59118174" xml:lang="en">Levi ben Gershom</persName>
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/59118174" xml:lang="he">לוי בן גרשם </persName>
							</author>
							<note>
								<p>Contains a preface which does not occur in the printed editions of the treatise. </p>
								<p>Contains author's statement which confirms that the commentary was completed on the <date calendar="Hebrew">3 Iyar 5098</date> (<date calendar="Gregorian">1338</date>). </p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Parchment codex of probably 15th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<support>Parchment codex.</support>
								<extent rend="visible">109 folios <dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>213</height>
										<width>150</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>145</height>
										<width>93</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>109 folios (+ 4 paper flyleaves at the beginning, 1 paper and 1 vellum flyleaf at the end).</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>11 quires of 10 leaves each.</p>
									<p>Quires signed with Hebrew letters on the first and last pages.</p>
								</collation>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout ruledLines="26" writtenLines="26" columns="1">
									<p>Uniform layout. </p>
									<p>Punctuated and accentuated biblical text is embedded.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Sefardi square and semi-cursive script, unpunctuated. Probably of 15th century.</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole"/>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>Folio iii recto: owner's Hebrew inscription: <q>לה' הארץ ומלואה מקנת כספי אברהם יצ בן לאא שלמה מפאנו זצ"ל</q>.</p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="censor">Camillo Jaghel</name>: inscribed with his name, <date calendar="Gregorian">1611</date>, Lugo; see <ref target="Popper_1969" type="page">50-56</ref>.</p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">Shelomoh Refa᾿el da Fano</name>: inscribed with his name in the owner's note, folio 1r and <name type="person" role="owner">Avraham ben Shelomoh da Fano</name>, inscribed, folio iii recto.</p>
						</additions>
						<bindingDesc>
							<binding>
								<p>Post-1600; Harleian binding of ivory leather.</p>
								<p>Spine: 'Perush Ralbag. R. Levi. Prov. Com. Hebrew. Brit. Mus. Ms. Harl. 7622. Pr. XXVIII.'</p>
								<p>Boxed.</p>
							</binding>
						</bindingDesc>
